  "text": "Eukaryotic nucleolar 60S ribosome assembly is conceptually reminiscent of early prokaryotic 50S assembly intermediates in which different rRNA domains are assembled in a modular fashion [CITATION_1] ( Fig. 4 , Extended Data Fig. 7) . However, our structures of nucleolar pre-60S particles highlight the high degree of control that is exerted to prevent the premature formation of inter-domain contacts of ribosomal RNA. They further illustrate how the reduction of conformational freedom and ordered sequence of assembly factors are enforced during assembly. These are overarching themes of the nucleolar stages for both the small and large ribosomal subunit assembly [CITATION_2] .",
